x4freetext: The 14C target was a self-supporting 280 mu-g/cm2
in the experiment. An ionization chamber was used as a
common DeltaE-detector for two telescopes to detect
particles with charge Z>2 whereas in the third
telescope consisted of a 40 mu-m silicon
DeltaE-detector was used to detect reaction products
with charge of Z=3 and 4 resolved.
